Package it.unicam.cs.pa.jbudget105053.model

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Account
    This interface extends the interface HasID and is implemented by all the classes that have the responsibility to manage an account.
    HasID
    This interface is implemented by all classes whose objects have a unique ID field that identifies them.
    Ledger
    This interface is implemented by all the classes that have the responsibility to manage all data of the application.
    Movement
    This interface extends the interface HasID and is implemented by all the classes that have the responsibility to manage a single movement.
    Tag
    This interface extends the interface HasID and is implemented by all the classes that have the responsibility to define a tag/category.
    Transaction
    This interface extends the interface HasID and is implemented by all the classes that have the responsibility to manage a transaction.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BasicAccount
    This class implements the interface Account and has the responsibility of managing a basic account.
    BasicMovement
    This class implements the interface Movement and has the responsibility of managing a single basic movement.
    BasicTag
    This class implements the interface Tag and has the responsibility of defining a tag/category.
    BasicTransaction
    This class implements the interface Transaction and has the responsibility of managing a basic transaction.
    Indexer
    This class has the responsibility to manage all IDs of all the accounts, tags, transactions and movements of the application.
    LedgerMenu
    This class implements the interface Ledger and has the responsibility to manage all data of the application.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    AccountType
    This enumeration defines the two types an Account can be: an ASSET or a LIABILITY.
    MovementType
    This enumeration defines the two types a Movement can be: an INCREMENT or a DECREMENT.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    MovementException
    This class extends the class Exception and has the responsibility to provide description for all possible errors deriving from the creation/removal of a movement.
